 Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Wauchope","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from either of two places in Scotland: Wauchopedale in Dumfriesshire or Wauchope in Hobkirk (Roxburghshire). The placename is from Old English <i>wala hop</i> ‘valley of the Welshmen’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret de Wauchope was born about 1355, in Langholm, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, her father, ALEXANDER WAUCHOPE, was 27 and her mother, Mrs Alexander Wauchope, was 25. She married Sir Adam Glendonwyn in 1368, in Parton, Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 6 sons. She died in Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1355–":"umbes 1355–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1355–1407":"1355–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1378–1437":"1378–1437","1379–Male":"1379–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1383–1402":"1383–1402","1385–1408":"1385–1408","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1332–Female":"1332–Surnud","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","1380":"1380","1437":"1437","1402":"1402","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1355":"1355","1332":"1332","about 1355":"umbes 1355","1408":"1408","1407":"1407","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Langholm, Dumfries, Scotland":"Langholm, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Westerkirk, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Westerkirk, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Parton, Kirkcudbrightshire, Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Parton, Dumfries and Galloway, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1355–":"noin 1355–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1355–1407":"1355–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1378–1437":"1378–1437","1379–Male":"1379–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1383–1402":"1383–1402","1385–1408":"1385–1408","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1332–Female":"1332–Kuollut","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","1380":"1380","1437":"1437","1402":"1402","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1355":"1355","1332":"1332","about 1355":"noin 1355","1408":"1408","1407":"1407","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Langholm, Dumfries, Scotland":"Langholm, Dumfriesshire, Sc